43 (__GNUC__ == 2 && __GNUC_MINOR__ >= 5))
44#define __LA_DEAD __attribute__((__noreturn__))

46#define __LA_DEAD

49#define ARCHIVE_WRITE_MAGIC (0xb0c5c0deU)
50#define ARCHIVE_READ_MAGIC (0xdeb0c5U)
51#define ARCHIVE_WRITE_DISK_MAGIC (0xc001b0c5U)
52#define ARCHIVE_READ_DISK_MAGIC (0xbadb0c5U)
53#define ARCHIVE_MATCH_MAGIC (0xcad11c9U)
54
55#define ARCHIVE_STATE_NEW 1U
56#define ARCHIVE_STATE_HEADER 2U
57#define ARCHIVE_STATE_DATA 4U
58#define ARCHIVE_STATE_EOF 0x10U
59#define ARCHIVE_STATE_CLOSED 0x20U
60#define ARCHIVE_STATE_FATAL 0x8000U
61#define ARCHIVE_STATE_ANY (0xFFFFU & ~ARCHIVE_STATE_FATAL)
62
63struct archive_vtable {
64 int (*archive_close)(struct archive *);
65 int (*archive_free)(struct archive *);
66 int (*archive_write_header)(struct archive *,
67 struct archive_entry *);
68 int (*archive_write_finish_entry)(struct archive *);
69 ssize_t (*archive_write_data)(struct archive *,
70 const void *, size_t);
71 ssize_t (*archive_write_data_block)(struct archive *,
72 const void *, size_t, int64_t);
73
74 int (*archive_read_next_header)(struct archive *,
75 struct archive_entry **);
76 int (*archive_read_next_header2)(struct archive *,
77 struct archive_entry *);
78 int (*archive_read_data_block)(struct archive *,
79 const void **, size_t *, int64_t *);
80
81 int (*archive_filter_count)(struct archive *);
82 int64_t (*archive_filter_bytes)(struct archive *, int);
83 int (*archive_filter_code)(struct archive *, int);
84 const char * (*archive_filter_name)(struct archive *, int);
85};
86
87struct archive_string_conv;
88
89struct archive {
90 /*
91 * The magic/state values are used to sanity-check the
92 * client's usage. If an API function is called at a
93 * ridiculous time, or the client passes us an invalid
94 * pointer, these values allow me to catch that.
95 */
96 unsigned int magic;
97 unsigned int state;
98
99 /*
100 * Some public API functions depend on the "real" type of the
101 * archive object.
102 */
103 struct archive_vtable *vtable;
104
105 int archive_format;
106 const char *archive_format_name;
107
108 int compression_code; /* Currently active compression. */
109 const char *compression_name;
110
111 /* Number of file entries processed. */
112 int file_count;
113
114 int archive_error_number;
115 const char *error;
116 struct archive_string error_string;
117
118 char *current_code;
119 unsigned current_codepage; /* Current ACP(ANSI CodePage). */
120 unsigned current_oemcp; /* Current OEMCP(OEM CodePage). */
121 struct archive_string_conv *sconv;
122
123 /*
124 * Used by archive_read_data() to track blocks and copy
125 * data to client buffers, filling gaps with zero bytes.
126 */
127 const char *read_data_block;
128 int64_t read_data_offset;
129 int64_t read_data_output_offset;
130 size_t read_data_remaining;
131
132 /*
133 * Used by formats/filters to determine the amount of data
134 * requested from a call to archive_read_data(). This is only
135 * useful when the format/filter has seek support.
136 */
137 char read_data_is_posix_read;
138 size_t read_data_requested;
139};
140
141/* Check magic value and state; return(ARCHIVE_FATAL) if it isn't valid. */
142int __archive_check_magic(struct archive *, unsigned int magic,
143 unsigned int state, const char *func);
144#define archive_check_magic(a, expected_magic, allowed_states, function_name) \
145 do { \
146 int magic_test = __archive_check_magic((a), (expected_magic), \
147 (allowed_states), (function_name)); \
148 if (magic_test == ARCHIVE_FATAL) \
149 return ARCHIVE_FATAL; \
150 } while (0)
151
152void __archive_errx(int retvalue, const char *msg) __LA_DEAD;
153
154void __archive_ensure_cloexec_flag(int fd);
155int __archive_mktemp(const char *tmpdir);
156
157int __archive_clean(struct archive *);
158
159void __archive_reset_read_data(struct archive *);
160
161#define err_combine(a,b) ((a) < (b) ? (a) : (b))
